idth of each layer to minimize latency while maintaining accuracy.\n   - **Evaluation Metrics**: Inference latency, memory usage, top-1 and top-5 accuracy.', '2. **Precision-Optimized Layer-Skipping**:\n   - **Procedure**: Develop a mechanism to selectively skip layers based on real-time latency constraints and precision requirements. Use a Jacobian-based layer-skipping framework to minimize hidden-state perturbation and enforce strict wall-clock budgets.\n   - **Evaluation Metrics**: Inference latency, memory usage, top-1 and top-5 accuracy.', '3. **Combined LOAMP Framework**:\n   - **Procedure**: Integrate latency-aware AMP quantization and precision-optimized layer-skipping into a unified framework. Evaluate the combined framework on the same models and dataset.\n   - **Evaluation Metrics**: Inference latency, memory usage, top-1 and top-5 accuracy.', '4. **Ablation Studies**:\n   - **Procedure**: Conduct ablation studies to isolate the contributions of latency-aware AMP quantization and precision-optimized layer-skipping.\n   - **Evaluation Metrics**: Inference latency, memory usage, top-1 and top-5 accuracy.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': '1. **Complexity of Real-Time Latency Optimization**: The dynamic adjustment of bit-widths and layer-skipping may introduce additional complexity and overhead.\n2. **Generalization to Different Models and Datasets**: The proposed framework may require fine-tuning for different ViT architectures and datasets.\n3. **Hardware Compatibility**: The effectiveness of LOAMP may vary across different hardware platforms due to differences in latency and memory constraints.\n4. **Quantization Error Propagation**: The cumulative effect of quantization errors across layers could impact model accuracy, especially in deep ViT architectures.'}
