Proposal finalized: {'Name': 'curvatureawareprecisionrouting', 'Title': 'Curvature-Aware Precision Routing for Efficient and Stable Neural Network Training', 'Short Hypothesis': 'A curvature-aware precision routing framework can dynamically adjust numerical precision during training, leading to more stable and efficient neural network optimization, while maintaining or improving model accuracy.', 'Related Work': 'Recent works such as Mix-GEMM (Reggiani et al., 2023) and Tri-Accel (Sheibanian et al., 2025) have explored mixed-precision training and hardware-software co-design to improve computational efficiency and numerical stability. However, these approaches often treat precision as a static choice or lack a formal mechanism to dynamically adjust precision based on the curvature of the loss landscape. Our proposal introduces a curvature-aware precision routing framework that leverages Hessian information to dynamically switch precision, providing a more theoretically grounded and adaptive solution.', 'Abstract': 'We propose a curvature-aware precision routing framework for neural network training that dynamically adjusts numerical precision based on the curvature of the loss landscape. This approach aims to balance computational efficiency and numerical stability by promoting higher precision in regions of high curvature and maintaining lower precision in flatter regions. We introduce a precision controller that uses Hessian information to adapt precision levels, ensuring that the training process remains stable and efficient. Through systematic experiments on benchmark datasets, we demonstrate that our method matches or exceeds the performance of full precision training while reducing computational overhead. This work bridges the gap between theoretical optimization and practical resource constraints, providing a mathematically transparent and computationally efficient solution.', 'Experiments': ['1. **Hessian Estimation and Precision Control**: Evaluate the effectiveness of Hessian-based precision control on a variety of neural network architectures (e.g., ResNet, LSTM) using popular datasets (e.g., CIFAR-10, IMDb Reviews). Measure the impact on training stability, convergence speed, and final model accuracy.', '2. **Computational Efficiency Analysis**: Compare the computational overhead and memory usage of our curvature-aware precision routing framework against static mixed-precision and full precision training. Use profiling tools to quantify the reduction in training time and memory usage.', '3. **Ablation Studies**: Conduct ablation studies to isolate the effects of different components of the precision controller, such as the Hessian estimator and precision switching thresholds. Evaluate the impact on model performance and resource utilization.', '4. **Generalization and Robustness**: Assess the generalization performance of models trained with our framework on unseen data and under different conditions (e.g., varying batch sizes, learning rates). Compare the robustness of our method to adversarial attacks and noisy data.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['1. **Hessian Estimation Complexity**: Accurately estimating the Hessian can be computationally expensive, especially for large models. We will need to develop efficient approximation techniques to keep the overhead manageable.', '2. **Hyperparameter Sensitivity**: The performance of the precision controller may be sensitive to the choice of hyperparameters, such as the precision switching thresholds. Careful tuning and validation will be required.', '3. **Limited Applicability**: The effectiveness of curvature-aware precision routing may vary across different types of neural networks and datasets. Additional experiments will be needed to validate the generalizability of our approach.', '4. **Hardware Constraints**: The proposed framework may require specialized hardware support for efficient Hessian computation and precision switching, which may not be available in all environments.']}
